        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 6:53PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 653 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from near Deadmans Basin Reservoir to 16
miles north of Columbus, or extending from 23 miles east of
Harlowton to 16 miles north of Columbus, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ryegate, Deadmans Basin Reservoir, Broadview, Lavina, Hailstone
Wildlife Refuge, Halfbreed Lake Wildlife, Rapelje, Franklin, Molt,
Comanche, Acton and Shawmut.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
